===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{UK}} A device which creates 'Logs' out of burnable waste; the device encases the burnable waste within a newspaper wrapping by the use of a special tube and plunger.
#: The inventor Arthur Howell wanted a way to burn initially sawdust efficiently and compactly and after many trial devices invented the <b>Logmaker</b>.
#: The <b>Logmaker</b> can burn any waste (cardboard, paper, wood shavings and sawdust and garden burnable waste) it helps reduce household waste and waste going to landfill and saves on fuel costs.